Known as "the Butcher" for his brutality during the rule of the Khmer Rouge, the commander remains popular in this remote former fort of the Khmer Rouge in northwestern Cambodia, where he built hospitals, bridges and other infrastructures, and where thousands of former soldiers of the organization still live.
