However, he emphasized "it is the madmen and the liars who imagine best" and it is where reality and lies converge, where it is no longer known that the narrative belongs to one side or another, where fictional literature reaches its peak.
He actually calls it the "cervantine tradition."
"By his inheritance we are what is told."
In her turn, writer Mayra Montero outlined and applauded the variety of interpretations that gave rise to the invitation of the FIL with its round table The finger on the sore.
