"I believe that good literature, good poetry, good songs contain a tacit commitment that of course is not premeditated," he said, after quoting that the reality of literature is communication and the dimension of the commitment that is established between author and readers, and that in a "chemical reaction" of the latter.
The evening was closed by the Spanish poet Luis García Montero whose intervention also emphasized "that finger in the wound of the writer's committed writer".
