Fourteen suspected drug traffickers arrested
On Wednesday, in Estrie, a dozen persecutions were carried out as part of the dismantling of a Cannabis production and sales network.
Fourteen people have been arrested and will face various charges.
Persecutions have taken place in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mainly where drug production took place.
"About 750 Cannabis plants, four kilos of hashish, money and equipment for production have been seized," says Louis-Philippe Ruel, Quebec Security spokesman.
In total, eleven men and three women have been arrested, including the two alleged network leaders, two men from Sherbrooke.
The detainees had to appear at the Sherbrooke courthouse within hours of their arrest.
They could face accusations of Cannabis production, possession with the aim of trafficking, plotting and theft of services, among others.
These persecutions have followed a long investigation that has lasted for about a year.
"It was the information provided by the public that allowed us to make the arrests," said Mr.Ruel.
This police operation involved around seventy officers from the Quebec Security Estrie investigation module, the Sherbrooke Police Service and the Memphrémagog Police Department.
